survey_response.review_text:
Pros : 
1. Experienced Doctor, Answers your all queries and doubts, never scare the patient.
2. Smiling Face.

Cons : 
1. She is very busy as deputed as HOD  in Columbia Asia  because  of that to connect her over phone is very tough, first you need to call hospital, they will connect you to her if required.

2. I suggest her name for consultation but not for delivery as she is too busy and cant give too much time to try for normal delivery .
As every girl is little scared of labour pain and want to opt C - section as painless option, Doctor tries to convince the pateint once or twice for normal else agreed for C-section.

3. She won't prefer Saturday and Sunday for deliveries.

I am totally happy and satisfied with Dr.Beena's treatment. I cannot say enough wonderful things about her. ***** ** **** * ***** ***** * ********* ****** *** ******** All I can say is I was so lucky to have found her. I only regret for not having seen or met her much before , I got to know about this amazing doctor through a friend of mine and I will strongly recommend all those with gynaec issues to meet Dr.Beena without any second thought or opinion. She will find a solution for you, a permanent solution. I can guarantee on that.  She never made me feel uncomfortable or bad for asking so many questions. Each time I see her, she has a smile on her face, no matter how big or complicated your problem is, she will make you feel at ease and give you the perfect treatment. I have always walked out from the clinic with great peace and contentment, thats how she makes you feel.  She is a best gyne I ever experienced. Before meeting Dr.Beena, I have consulted with many other gyne who are just professional with their patients. However, Dr. Beena is out of the world I would say. **** *** ***** Hats off to you Doctor... I would once  again recommend everyone to consult doctor Beena and get best advice all the time. God Bless you Doctor...
She listened the problem patiently. Gone through all reports. She did a physical check tge explained what's issue, what yo be done. She is very calm and gave enough support.

Dr Beena does not give you the time of day which can be very disappointing for new mothers. I had to consult with Dr Beena as my previous consulting gynecologist left the hospital. Dr Beena is very brisk and curt and none of our sessions lasted more than 5 mins. Any follow up questions is given a standard response. At the time of birth, I did not have a say as to the type of birth. Worst still we did not receive any prior information about what a c-section entails. I had to do all my research on google. And after delivery too I had to google everything. I stopped visiting after the delivery however, unfortunately I developed infection at the site of sutures and had high fever. My wound opened up again. It took months of going to the hospital to get it dressed till it finally healed. 
That was very taxing especially if you have a newborn to look after and you are running on minimal sleep. 
We plan to have just one child. And I feel cheated that my only experience of pregnancy has not been a very happy one.

Beena Ma'am is very confident experienced doctor, *** ****** **** *********** ******** ** ***** *******, she has a very good approach to.go step by step for patients welfare. She was very helpful for me in my consultation pregnancy phase and delivery, never scares patients and take correct action. I am thankful to her.

An excellent doctor. I've visited Dr. Beena 3-4 times and every time I have come out with a sigh of relief. She listens patiently and always have a smile on her face.. very comforting. She does not rush into anything and Very calmly does the diagnosis.. her treatment worked really good for me.
After a long search found a very reliable doctor.
Thank you Dr. Beena

Doctor was good. However for an aptt booked for 12 pm, got to see the doctor only by around 1 after mutliple follow ups with reception. Resulted in an hour of delay for a non critical issue. Hospital should have better way of tracking appointments and avoid over booking.

I visited beena for my pregnancy and she is friendly and nvr suggested any unneccassary tests and she supported me during my labour and eventhough its c section she showed me baby and advised me for early breastfeeding after 3hrs from c section.she helped me in fast recovery .Thanks beena for her support.

Dr.Beena has been very patient and friendly and throughout my pregnancy took real good care and was always available over phone. Very compassionate.. She took extra care during my last few weeks of pregnancy when my BP levels were fluctuating. Highly recommend her for pregnancy and delivery related issues.

I was completely relaxed throughout the surgery. Dr.Beena took extra care when my BP levels were fluctuating in the last few days of pregnancy.

I felt really happy and comfortable with the warmth shown by Dr. Beena. Although it's little little far from electronic City I would like to visit Dr Beena as I am extremely satisfied with the way I am treated by her.

She gave a genuine advise to me & I was completely relieved. I will recommend her for sure.

I went for my wife's pregnancy to Dr. Beena. She is a great doctor who knows what she is doing. My wife had low AFI during 37th week. She took a decision to induce labor pains.. She tried her best to deliver normally.  We were blessed with a healthy baby delivered normally.

Dr Beena has been very supportive throughout my pregnancy. Her suggestion are bang on. I had faith in her and she didn’t let me down. She gave me  positive hopes throughout. She also handled my sisters critical pre- mature delivery , her timely decisions have blessed us with babies.  A big thanks to her!

One of the Great gynecologist and a caring human being. Due to her continuous suggestions and support we were able to get our second baby c-section delivery. Never seen a friendly-behavior and exceptional question answering. Thanks so much for assistance.

*** ****** ******** ** ****** ** **** ****** ****** ** *** ******* **** ** ** ********** She was the first doctor we consulted during pregnancy. *** **** ** ** **** *** asked for more and more scans for the hospital, till I had to rush to a nearby doctor with a severe stomach pain to find out that the baby was not growing, and it was a miscarriage. **** ****** **** **** ***** **** ******* ***** *** ****** *** ***** ** ***** *** ******* *** *** **** *** *** *** *** ****** ** ** **** *** ******** **** Extremely upset and hurt due to this. We recommend that no one goes through a situation like this.

*** ****** *** ** ********* ************** *** what good is that knowledge that you can't share with your patient and comfort them. Dr. Beena is extremely curt and to the point, spends less than a couple of minutes with every patient. Be prepared to Google everything to get your answers, because she is never interested in sharing anything. There is no transparency or information sharing. Every meeting with her leaves you dazed and confused. 
If you are the types who are ok doing whatever is recommended, she may be a great Doctor.
But, I repeat, if you are the kinds who would like to know more about the procedures etc., do not at all consider going to her. You'll leave highly unsatisfied.

She is very supportive we had a great journey with her during my pregnancy and delivery . Would surely recommend her :)

She listens and explains very nicely. Gives time to the patient and her experience shows in discussion.

She's very polite and friendly,when I met her first time that time am 3 months pregnant now my baby will get 3 yrs till now am continuing with her, she's like goddess for me,she saved me and my baby from those critical situations, now am alive means that is because of her. she's not like other doctors, Beena Mam is something special to me, now am planning for 2nd baby,started treatment with her....
